---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Trinidad Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/trinidad-and-tobago/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Barbados for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/barbados' },
  { title: 'Jamaica for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/jamaica' },
  { title: 'UK for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/united-kingdom' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'ttFit', header: 'T&T Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'TTD$3,300-4,715/mo', ttFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'TTD$3,870-5,525/mo', ttFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'TTD$2,970-4,235/mo', ttFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'TTD$2,760-3,940/mo', ttFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Sagicor/TATIL', entryAge: '65', renewal: 'Varies', monthlyFrom: 'TTD$1,500-3,000/mo', ttFit: 'Local Option' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'TTD$2,970-4,715', annual: 'TTD$35,640-56,580' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'TTD$4,075-6,290', annual: 'TTD$48,900-75,480' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'TTD$5,490-8,460', annual: 'TTD$65,880-101,520' },
  { category: 'Local Private Insurance', monthly: 'TTD$1,500-3,000/mo', annual: 'TTD$18,000-36,000' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Stay', monthly: 'TTD$8,000-15,000/day', annual: 'Per incident' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Trinidad and Tobago 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Trinidad and Tobago. Caribbean culture, oil wealth, English-speaking, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Trinidad and Tobago"
  subheadline="Trinidad and Tobago offers rich Caribbean culture, oil-based economy, English language, and proximity to South America—a culturally vibrant retirement option with improving healthcare."
  heroImage="/images/countries/trinidad-and-tobago-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Trinidad and Tobago</h2>
  <p>
    Trinidad and Tobago offers rich multicultural heritage (Carnival!), English language, oil wealth, and affordable living. For those with T&T heritage or seeking Caribbean culture beyond beaches, this twin-island nation delivers character that tourist destinations lack.
  </p>

  <p>
    Trinidad has Port of Spain capital with services and culture. Tobago offers quieter beach lifestyle and tourism focus. T&T is more developed than most Caribbean nations due to oil/gas industry. Safety varies by area; research locations carefully.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Improving; private hospitals available</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> English</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> TTD$12,000-25,000/month (~$1,800-3,700 USD); moderate</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Tropical; warm year-round; outside hurricane belt</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Multicultural; festive; oil economy</li>
      <li><strong>Diaspora:</strong> Large T&T diaspora in US, UK, Canada</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Trinidad and Tobago Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    T&T healthcare is improving—Eric Williams Medical Sciences Complex is the main public teaching hospital. Private options include St. Clair Medical Centre, Westshore Medical, and Medical Associates. Quality varies; oil wealth has funded infrastructure improvements.
  </p>

  <p>
    Public healthcare is free but stretched. Private hospitals provide better experience. Some specialists available; complex cases may require Miami or elsewhere. Private insurance essential for quality care. Medical tourism to Miami is common.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Private Care Essential</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Public healthcare in T&T is available but overcrowded. Private hospitals offer significantly better service. International insurance with US evacuation recommended for complex conditions. Miami is approximately 4 hours by air.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Trinidad and Tobago offers residence options:
  </p>

  <h3>Returning Nationals</h3>
  <p>
    T&T citizens returning home. Most straightforward option for diaspora.
  </p>

  <h3>Permanent Residence</h3>
  <p>
    After 5 years legal residence. Various pathways including family, employment, investment.
  </p>

  <h3>CARICOM Single Market</h3>
  <p>
    CARICOM nationals can work and live. Various categories and requirements.
  </p>

  <h3>Visitor Entry</h3>
  <p>
    Many nationalities receive 90-day entry. Extensions possible. Some use extended visits.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for T&T:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Residence:</strong> Private health insurance strongly recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Public option:</strong> Available but quality varies</li>
    <li><strong>Private essential:</strong> For quality care access</li>
    <li><strong>US evacuation:</strong> Include Miami coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for T&T</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance with private T&T and US coverage recommended. Local insurers (Sagicor, TATIL) may have age limits. Ensure Miami evacuation included for complex conditions. Private hospitals in T&T are good for routine care.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in T&T, private coverage essential:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for T&T</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Americas coverage, strong network</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), worldwide</li>
    <li><strong>Sagicor:</strong> Regional leader but age limits</li>
    <li><strong>Private T&T hospitals:</strong> Good for routine care</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage for Trinidad and Tobago.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs in T&T (TTD ~6.8 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Local for routine:</strong> Sagicor/TATIL if eligible by age</li>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> Reduce international plan costs</li>
    <li><strong>Tobago living:</strong> Generally more affordable than Trinidad</li>
    <li><strong>Public backup:</strong> Available for emergencies</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: Returning Trini-American, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $3,500/month pension. T&T citizenship. Diego Martin.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global with Americas + Medicare for US visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~TTD$3,800/month. Coming home; US healthcare backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British-Trini Retiree, 71</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> £3,000/month pension. Dual citizenship. Tobago.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with UK and Caribbean coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~TTD$4,500/month. Island lifestyle; UK healthcare option.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Canadian-Trini, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> C$4,000/month pension. Returning national. Port of Spain.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care + maintain provincial coverage for visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~TTD$3,200/month. Caribbean home; Canadian backup.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Trinidad and Tobago safe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Mixed—certain areas of Port of Spain have crime concerns. Tobago is generally safer. Research specific neighborhoods. Many expats live safely with normal precautions. Not like tourist-focused Caribbean islands; more real.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Trinidad vs Tobago for retirement?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Trinidad has better healthcare, more services, urban life. Tobago is quieter, more touristy, beautiful beaches. Many split time between both. Healthcare facilities concentrated in Trinidad; consider this for seniors.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is T&T outside hurricane belt?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Mostly yes—southern Caribbean location provides protection. Hurricanes rarely make direct hits. Still prepare for tropical weather. Climate advantage over northern Caribbean islands.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about cost of living?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Moderate—cheaper than Barbados or Cayman. Oil economy means some imported goods are subsidized. Budget TTD$12,000-20,000/month (~$1,800-3,000) for comfortable living. Tobago may be slightly cheaper.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for T&T coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with T&T authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
